<javascript-typescript-indentation>

<title>JavaScript/TypeScript Indentation Standards</title>

<rules>
- Always use 2 spaces for indentation
- Never use tabs
- Configure editor to insert spaces when tab key is pressed
- Each nested level increases indentation by exactly 2 spaces
- Maintain consistent indentation throughout the file
- Apply to all .js, .jsx, .ts, .tsx, .mjs, and .cjs files
</rules>

